  "texts": [
    "To this end, we focused on lung adenocarcinoma, a cancer type that has been shown to consist of an oftentimes complex mix of diverse histologic patterns (notably lepidic/in situ, acinar, papillary, cribriform, solid, and micropapillary), which are strongly linked to clinical outcomes 1.",
    "We applied HPL to whole-slide images of lung adenocarcinomas obtained from TCGA.",
    "The slides were first split into tiles at 5x magnification, 224 × 224 pixels (2μm/px) in size.",
    "Tiles with more than 40% of background were filtered out (considering background pixels those which average grey-level is above 230 -Note that this will result in removal of some tiles at the edge of the tissue as well as some loose tissue regions).",
    "First, we sub-sampled 250,000K tiles for the selfsupervised task."
  ],
